cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with machine reading comprehension tasks and proposes a new model for the same. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper introduces a new optimization approach using reinforcement learning. 
3. cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new model that enhances previous attentive readers. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the proposed model uses neural networks for machine reading comprehension. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category as the proposed model uses attention mechanisms and alignment architecture, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
